1
00:00:12,385 --> 00:00:13,224
Rahul?

2
00:00:13,305 --> 00:00:15,705
- There seems to be some misunderstanding.
- Come.

3
00:00:15,785 --> 00:00:17,625
This packet does not belong to…

4
00:00:17,705 --> 00:00:19,945
We will talk. Get in the car.

5
00:00:20,025 --> 00:00:22,025
What… what is happening here?

6
00:00:22,105 --> 00:00:25,705
Officer, please, please, please.
Let me explain you this.

7
00:00:25,785 --> 00:00:28,705
The car was mine,
but the packet was not mine.

8
00:00:28,785 --> 00:00:31,425
Hey! Why? Why can't you…

9
00:00:32,825 --> 00:00:34,745
- Let me make a call.
- No calls.

10
00:00:34,825 --> 00:00:35,745
Calm down!

11
00:00:36,625 --> 00:00:39,025
- Let… let me make a call, please.
- No call.

12
00:00:39,105 --> 00:00:40,345
Why don't you listen to me?

13
00:00:40,425 --> 00:00:43,545
Enough! Don't irritate me.

14
00:00:47,545 --> 00:00:48,745
Where are you taking her?

15
00:00:48,825 --> 00:00:50,985
Where are you taking her?
Where are you taking me?

16
00:00:51,065 --> 00:00:53,305
Shut up!

17
00:00:53,385 --> 00:00:55,745
Hey, are you listening to me?

18
00:00:55,825 --> 00:00:56,665
Where are we going?

19
00:00:56,745 --> 00:00:57,905
Shut up!

20
00:00:57,985 --> 00:01:00,145
Telling you right now,
stop the fucking car!

21
00:01:00,705 --> 00:01:03,145
This is the desert.
What are we doing here?

22
00:01:03,225 --> 00:01:04,945
We're doing the right thing.

23
00:01:05,025 --> 00:01:06,705
Officer, will you explain me?

24
00:01:06,785 --> 00:01:07,625
Shut up!

25
00:01:09,424 --> 00:01:13,545
There is simply nothing around me.
Stop the car.

26
00:01:27,585 --> 00:01:28,785
Hey, man! Watch it!

27
00:01:28,865 --> 00:01:31,065
My batch has been assigned
to serve the delegates.

28
00:01:31,145 --> 00:01:33,105
But why are you complaining?

29
00:01:33,185 --> 00:01:35,345
Have fun in the 5-star hotel for five days

30
00:01:35,425 --> 00:01:38,065
and then you can catch the smugglers.

31
00:01:38,145 --> 00:01:42,185
It's not like smuggling is going to
stop at this airport, right? Shake on it.

32
00:02:01,065 --> 00:02:02,545
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Arjun dear.

33
00:02:02,625 --> 00:02:04,825
Govind, I have something urgent.

34
00:02:04,905 --> 00:02:08,385
<i>Our COIN officer</i>
<i>managed to separate Priya from Rahul</i>

35
00:02:08,465 --> 00:02:10,905
<i>and put her on a flight to Mumbai.</i>

36
00:02:10,985 --> 00:02:15,265
<i>And made sure that Rahul could not</i>
<i>get in touch with anyone for a few hours.</i>

37
00:02:20,025 --> 00:02:20,865
For you.

38
00:02:34,265 --> 00:02:38,185
Officer, what are we doing here?
This is a completely deserted area.

39
00:02:38,265 --> 00:02:40,585
The place I am taking you to,
you will like it. Shut up!

40
00:02:40,665 --> 00:02:42,105
Can I call my uncle, please?

41
00:02:42,185 --> 00:02:45,825
Listen, Officer, this can escalate
to the higher, higher, higher authorities.

42
00:02:45,905 --> 00:02:46,745
Silent!

43
00:02:46,825 --> 00:02:50,545
I'm telling you this right now.
You don't want to mess with me.

44
00:02:50,625 --> 00:02:52,425
Shut up!

45
00:02:53,705 --> 00:02:57,505
Enough, Enough. Don't irritate me.

46
00:02:59,105 --> 00:03:00,745
Let us take him out of reach…

47
00:03:01,745 --> 00:03:02,905
I'll show you.

48
00:03:04,585 --> 00:03:06,345
- Why did you stop here?
- Come.

49
00:03:06,425 --> 00:03:09,385
- Why did you stop?
- Just get down. Go!

50
00:03:11,865 --> 00:03:14,585
Officer! Officer!

51
00:03:21,425 --> 00:03:22,305
Fuck!

52
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:27,145
Arbab, connect to the police station
in 10 minutes.

53
00:04:27,585 --> 00:04:29,585
Please.

54
00:04:29,665 --> 00:04:32,265
<i>- What about the consignment?</i>
- Don't worry about that.

55
00:04:32,345 --> 00:04:35,345
Yes, Suresh is handling that.
Please come to the police station. Hurry.

56
00:04:35,425 --> 00:04:36,825
Okay.

57
00:04:38,185 --> 00:04:39,865
Gentlemen, excuse me.

58
00:04:39,945 --> 00:04:42,065
- Sure. Sure.
<i>- Inshallah, Inshallah.</i>

59
00:04:53,865 --> 00:04:54,705
Fuck!

60
00:05:02,945 --> 00:05:05,785
- Sir, is mine done?
- Just a sec. You may go.

61
00:05:25,105 --> 00:05:28,585
- Mr. and Mrs. Sharma.
- Yes, sir.

62
00:05:28,665 --> 00:05:29,865
Here. Your tickets.

63
00:05:30,945 --> 00:05:33,265
After clearing check-in
and security check,

64
00:05:33,345 --> 00:05:36,985
you will go into the washroom,
next to duty-free.

65
00:05:37,065 --> 00:05:41,025
Our janitors will meet you
in your respective washrooms,

66
00:05:41,105 --> 00:05:44,145
who will give you two packets each
after seeing your boarding passes.

67
00:05:44,225 --> 00:05:46,545
We have also booked wheelchairs for you.

68
00:05:46,625 --> 00:05:48,945
So you'll be the first to board the plane.

69
00:05:49,025 --> 00:05:50,145
- Okay.
- Is it clear?

70
00:06:04,025 --> 00:06:05,665
Just hold on. He's here.

71
00:06:05,745 --> 00:06:08,465
Let me talk to him and figure out.
Yes, just hold.

72
00:06:08,545 --> 00:06:10,545
<i>- Assalam-alaikum.</i>
<i>- Walaikum-assalam.</i>

73
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:12,505
I've tried everywhere to find a clue.

74
00:06:12,585 --> 00:06:14,185
But can't find as to who took them.

75
00:06:14,265 --> 00:06:16,385
- Please help me find out.
- Wait. Wait here.

76
00:06:17,265 --> 00:06:18,625
Yes, now tell me.

77
00:06:57,705 --> 00:07:00,945
<i>My team was handling the delegates'</i>
<i>protocol on the day of conference.</i>

78
00:07:01,025 --> 00:07:04,585
<i>And everything was going on</i>
<i>as I had intended and as per my plan.</i>

79
00:07:29,985 --> 00:07:31,945
- Yes.
<i>- Tell me. Any news?</i>

80
00:07:32,025 --> 00:07:33,705
No, Arbab has gone inside to find out.

81
00:07:33,785 --> 00:07:36,625
- Okay. Do call me when you figure out.
- Sure.

82
00:08:15,905 --> 00:08:19,465
<i>Good morning, ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>this is your captain from the flight deck.</i>

83
00:08:19,545 --> 00:08:22,625
<i>We are now ready</i>
<i>to depart from Milan to Mumbai.</i>

84
00:09:47,705 --> 00:09:51,345
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>we have now reached our cruising altitude.</i>

85
00:09:51,425 --> 00:09:53,945
<i>Seatbelt signs are now off,</i>

86
00:09:54,025 --> 00:09:57,665
<i>however for your safety,</i>
<i>please keep your belts securely fastened.</i>

87
00:09:57,745 --> 00:10:01,705
<i>You may now use your electronic devices.</i>
<i>We'll be coming to the cabin shortly</i>

88
00:10:01,785 --> 00:10:05,625
<i>with our in-flight service.</i>
<i>Sit back and relax and enjoy the flight.</i>

89
00:10:53,545 --> 00:10:54,665
We are ready to fly.

90
00:11:05,745 --> 00:11:10,545
Caught you.
Where are you running?

91
00:11:11,185 --> 00:11:12,905
Go! Go, go with Mumma. Go!

92
00:11:12,985 --> 00:11:15,225
Darling…

93
00:11:15,305 --> 00:11:17,585
- Are you hungry, my love?
- Yeah.

94
00:11:26,345 --> 00:11:27,185
Yeah.

95
00:11:29,705 --> 00:11:31,705
Okay. All right.

96
00:11:32,745 --> 00:11:36,185
Keep me posted, every second. Absolutely.

97
00:11:37,545 --> 00:11:39,985
Every bit of news. Yeah.

98
00:11:41,665 --> 00:11:45,865
Of course. All well. Okay, fine.

99
00:11:48,065 --> 00:11:49,865
- Cheers!
- All is under control.

100
00:11:52,305 --> 00:11:55,425
- Something is bothering me, Sharma <i>ji.</i>
- What? All is calm and quiet.

101
00:11:57,065 --> 00:11:58,545
A little too calm, isn't it?

102
00:11:59,625 --> 00:12:02,985
There's nothing like that.
You're just overthinking.

103
00:12:03,065 --> 00:12:04,105
Let me get some ice.

104
00:12:10,585 --> 00:12:13,665
Nobody is giving me any answers.
Nobody is saying anything.

105
00:12:13,745 --> 00:12:15,265
- Don't worry.
- How will we find out?

106
00:12:15,345 --> 00:12:18,065
Don't worry. It'll work out.
Have faith in the Lord.

107
00:12:18,705 --> 00:12:21,785
I do have faith, Arbab sahib.
But we need to find out.

108
00:12:21,865 --> 00:12:23,945
He… he's here too.

109
00:12:24,025 --> 00:12:26,745
What happened, Anna? Any news?

110
00:12:26,825 --> 00:12:28,985
This is the fourth police station.
No news.

111
00:12:29,065 --> 00:12:31,665
Arbab involved Omar sahib.

112
00:12:31,745 --> 00:12:33,625
- Has the consignment left?
- Yes.

113
00:12:34,465 --> 00:12:37,265
Flights will start landing in Mumbai soon.

114
00:13:06,785 --> 00:13:08,025
- Sir.
- Sir.

115
00:13:08,105 --> 00:13:08,945
- Sir.
- Pen?

116
00:13:09,665 --> 00:13:11,745
- Goodnight.
- All right, sir.

117
00:13:11,825 --> 00:13:13,825
- Mention the time.
- Sure, sir.

118
00:13:15,025 --> 00:13:16,505
Here. In this column.

119
00:13:23,025 --> 00:13:25,305
The flights will land soon, Patel sahib.

120
00:13:25,385 --> 00:13:27,665
- All well?
- Yes, Ramesh bhai.

121
00:13:27,745 --> 00:13:30,545
Our team is batting. Hang up.

122
00:13:31,705 --> 00:13:34,025
Patel sir, Prakash sir is calling you.

123
00:13:37,585 --> 00:13:40,105
I mean, he has called all of you, sir.

124
00:13:40,865 --> 00:13:41,985
Shall we?

125
00:13:43,345 --> 00:13:44,545
Let's go.

126
00:13:55,145 --> 00:13:56,865
- Sir.
- Sir.

127
00:13:57,985 --> 00:13:58,905
Please.

128
00:14:00,265 --> 00:14:03,585
We are about to launch an op today,
called Operation Longshot.

129
00:14:04,305 --> 00:14:07,505
We have specific intel
that Choudhary Syndicate is sending

130
00:14:07,585 --> 00:14:10,105
huge quantities
of drugs and gold to Mumbai.

131
00:14:10,185 --> 00:14:11,825
And a large consignment of luxury goods

132
00:14:11,905 --> 00:14:13,345
is also coming on the Milan flight.

133
00:14:13,425 --> 00:14:17,545
We also have intel that more than
50 couriers are going to land here today.

134
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:20,265
So all of you have to be super alert.

135
00:14:20,905 --> 00:14:23,025
Especially the officers who'll be in line.

136
00:14:23,625 --> 00:14:26,665
Team, I want this op
to be a grand success.

137
00:14:30,225 --> 00:14:32,625
Arjun Meena will lead the operation.

138
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,145
Arjun, all yours.

139
00:14:39,505 --> 00:14:40,345
Sir.

140
00:15:10,745 --> 00:15:11,905
Wrist watch?

141
00:15:15,705 --> 00:15:17,945
This bag will be kept
in Prakash sir's cabin.

142
00:15:18,505 --> 00:15:21,825
In case of emergency,
you can use the landline in there.

143
00:15:22,785 --> 00:15:24,585
Based on intel
we'll be targeting 19 flights

144
00:15:24,665 --> 00:15:26,665
in the window of three and a half hours.

145
00:15:26,745 --> 00:15:28,225
But we have a situation.

146
00:15:28,305 --> 00:15:30,945
The last flight
from Middle East will take off

147
00:15:31,025 --> 00:15:33,425
half an hour
after the first flight lands here.

148
00:15:33,505 --> 00:15:37,385
So we have to let the first courier
pass through the green channel.

149
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:40,785
One of our teams along with DRI officers

150
00:15:40,865 --> 00:15:44,065
will follow them and arrest them
as soon as they get orders.

151
00:15:44,145 --> 00:15:47,185
Sajjad and Awasthi will be in that team.

152
00:15:47,265 --> 00:15:51,705
The team will be led by you, Patel sir.

153
00:15:57,265 --> 00:15:58,345
- Mitali,
- Yes, sir.

154
00:15:58,425 --> 00:16:00,265
- Shreelata, Dhuria…
- Yes, sir.

155
00:16:00,345 --> 00:16:02,065
…will be at the domestic airport

156
00:16:02,145 --> 00:16:04,745
because nine
of the 19 flights will land there.

157
00:16:05,585 --> 00:16:09,225
You will detain the passengers sitting
on the seat numbers marked in the list

158
00:16:09,305 --> 00:16:10,985
and get the gold from them.

159
00:16:12,065 --> 00:16:13,305
- Is it clear?
- Yes, sir.

160
00:16:13,385 --> 00:16:15,145
Gold in domestic flights?

161
00:16:19,185 --> 00:16:20,025
Let's go.

162
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:33,505
Meena!

163
00:16:39,505 --> 00:16:42,865
Do you and Prakash sir think that you guys
are the only honest officers here?

164
00:16:42,945 --> 00:16:46,225
And the rest of us are hand in glove
with the smugglers?

165
00:16:47,345 --> 00:16:50,945
No, Patel sahib.
I have full faith in your honesty.

166
00:16:57,225 --> 00:17:02,385
<i>- 555039, descend, maintain level 980.</i>
<i>- Sir, maintaining 980 for 555039.</i>

167
00:17:02,545 --> 00:17:05,625
<i>For left heading 300 report on localizer.</i>

168
00:17:21,585 --> 00:17:24,585
<i>Ladies and Gentlemen, welcome aboard</i>
<i>the flight from Lucknow to Mumbai.</i>

169
00:17:24,665 --> 00:17:27,704
<i>Our flight time is expected</i>
<i>to be two hours and ten minutes.</i>

170
00:17:32,224 --> 00:17:34,665
<i>Thank you and have a comfortable flight.</i>

171
00:17:34,745 --> 00:17:36,785
Vincent, you will be in line.

172
00:17:36,865 --> 00:17:40,265
And the rest will accompany me
to the arrival hall and green channel.

173
00:17:40,345 --> 00:17:41,265
Right.

174
00:17:41,345 --> 00:17:44,425
Sir. Sir, what does hand in glove mean?

175
00:17:47,225 --> 00:17:48,465
Mitali.

176
00:17:48,545 --> 00:17:52,425
Can you explain this kid
what hand in glove means?

177
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:54,465
Come on.

178
00:17:56,105 --> 00:17:57,265
Follow me, guys.

179
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:24,145
Eighteen flights are in the air,
only one to go.

180
00:19:24,945 --> 00:19:26,625
Get the photos of the passengers.

181
00:19:27,745 --> 00:19:29,625
{\an8}Can you swear on your kid

182
00:19:30,025 --> 00:19:32,185
{\an8}that you've never been hand in glove?

183
00:19:33,385 --> 00:19:37,585
You know, Mr. Ravi,
a government officer is as honest

184
00:19:37,665 --> 00:19:38,865
or corrupt as his boss.

185
00:19:38,945 --> 00:19:40,705
- You are right, ma'am.
- Come on.

186
00:19:40,785 --> 00:19:41,745
Let's go.

187
00:19:41,825 --> 00:19:43,465
- Dhuria.
- Yes, ma'am.

188
00:19:44,905 --> 00:19:46,705
You wanted to know about hand in glove?

189
00:19:46,785 --> 00:19:47,825
Yes, ma'am.

190
00:19:47,905 --> 00:19:48,985
Tell me something.

191
00:19:49,065 --> 00:19:52,705
What's the difference between
an honest officer and a corrupt officer?

192
00:19:52,785 --> 00:19:56,745
So, difference between the two, ma'am.
A corrupt officer--

193
00:19:57,425 --> 00:20:00,345
A corrupt officer takes bribe,
and honest one doesn't. It's very simple.

194
00:20:00,425 --> 00:20:01,345
Right, ma'am.

195
00:20:01,425 --> 00:20:04,665
What will a corrupt officer
say to a passenger he pulls aside?

196
00:20:05,425 --> 00:20:09,345
What will he say? He will say that…

197
00:20:09,425 --> 00:20:11,785
- Will he ask for a bribe?
- Dhuria.

198
00:20:12,705 --> 00:20:14,305
He won't say it to his face.

199
00:20:14,985 --> 00:20:17,785
We are customs officers.
We have some dignity, don't we?

200
00:20:17,865 --> 00:20:18,865
Right, ma'am.

201
00:20:18,945 --> 00:20:20,505
He will tell the passenger

202
00:20:20,585 --> 00:20:23,625
that you have been caught
for alleged evasion of a 100k custom duty.

203
00:20:24,465 --> 00:20:26,385
Now, what do you want to do?

204
00:20:26,465 --> 00:20:30,465
How do you want to do it? How much
do you want to give? That's hand in glove.

205
00:20:30,545 --> 00:20:33,825
- Oh, so this is what it is.
- Yes.

206
00:20:34,505 --> 00:20:37,305
- Okay.
- But forget this word here. Okay?

207
00:20:37,385 --> 00:20:39,865
- Or I will PK you.
- PK, ma'am?

208
00:20:41,225 --> 00:20:43,825
- I'll tell you some other day. Come on.
- Okay, ma'am.

209
00:20:59,345 --> 00:21:01,585
- Would you like to have something?
- No.

210
00:21:03,185 --> 00:21:05,865
No. Nobody… Nobody wants anything. Go, go.

211
00:21:06,625 --> 00:21:07,665
Okay, ma'am.

212
00:21:30,225 --> 00:21:31,145
Sir.

213
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:36,825
Go, get the checklist.

214
00:21:49,705 --> 00:21:52,665
- Just come when I call you. Okay?
- Okay, bhai.

215
00:22:04,145 --> 00:22:08,345
CHHATRAPATI SHIVAJI MAHARAJ
INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT

216
00:22:17,825 --> 00:22:22,145
Arjun! Here are the couriers
for the flight that is about to land.

217
00:22:28,945 --> 00:22:33,025
{\an8}<i>Ladies and gentlemen, welcome to Mumbai.</i>
<i>The local time is 20:25,</i>

218
00:22:33,105 --> 00:22:35,305
{\an8}<i>and the temperature is 27 degrees.</i>

219
00:22:35,385 --> 00:22:38,105
<i>Please remain seated</i>
<i>with your seatbelts fastened,</i>

220
00:22:38,185 --> 00:22:40,185
<i>until the seatbelts sign is turned off.</i>

221
00:22:40,265 --> 00:22:42,025
<i>Be carefull when opening overhead bins.</i>

222
00:22:42,105 --> 00:22:43,985
<i>As contents may have shifted</i>
<i>during the flight.</i>

223
00:22:44,065 --> 00:22:48,585
<i>On behalf of Sitaara and the entire team,</i>
<i>thank you for flying with us.</i>

224
00:22:48,665 --> 00:22:50,705
<i>We'd love to see you again soon.</i>

225
00:23:34,785 --> 00:23:38,945
<i>Assalam-alaikum,</i> Aslam bhai.
We got our baggage. Send for the car.

226
00:23:40,145 --> 00:23:41,945
No, there was no problem at all.

227
00:23:46,105 --> 00:23:48,265
- Yes, bhai. Okay, bhai.
- Get the car. Hurry.

228
00:23:54,065 --> 00:23:56,585
- Patel, come in.
- Yes, Patel here.

229
00:23:56,665 --> 00:23:58,305
Couriers have been identified.

230
00:23:58,385 --> 00:24:01,185
Two women with a little girl, and two men.

231
00:24:01,265 --> 00:24:02,785
Total five people in the group.

232
00:24:02,865 --> 00:24:04,465
They just passed the green channel.

233
00:24:04,545 --> 00:24:06,945
- Over and out.
- Roger that. Over and out.

234
00:24:46,145 --> 00:24:48,785
Awasthi! Awasthi!

235
00:24:48,865 --> 00:24:51,665
These people went straight
to parking in Departures.

236
00:24:51,745 --> 00:24:53,265
Get the car to Departures. Hurry!

237
00:24:53,345 --> 00:24:54,825
Sir, I'm stuck in traffic.

238
00:24:54,905 --> 00:24:57,225
It'll take me ten minutes
to reach Departures.

239
00:24:57,305 --> 00:24:58,585
Hey, move!

240
00:25:19,945 --> 00:25:22,065
Stop the car! Stop!

241
00:25:23,705 --> 00:25:26,425
- Sir, who are you?
- Follow that car! Follow that car!

242
00:25:26,505 --> 00:25:28,665
- But who are you, sir?
- See the ID and move!

243
00:25:28,745 --> 00:25:30,265
- Get moving!
- Yes, sir. I am.

244
00:25:31,025 --> 00:25:32,185
Patel, come in.

245
00:25:34,345 --> 00:25:35,825
Patel, come in.

246
00:25:39,185 --> 00:25:40,145
Shit.

247
00:25:44,985 --> 00:25:47,665
- Prakash sir, come in.
- Go, Arjun.

248
00:25:47,745 --> 00:25:50,025
One flight is yet to take off.

249
00:25:50,105 --> 00:25:51,865
We'll start the operation as soon it does.

250
00:25:51,945 --> 00:25:54,425
<i>And two domestic flights</i>
<i>are also about to land.</i>

251
00:25:54,505 --> 00:25:57,025
Can you delay them for ten minutes? Over.

252
00:25:57,105 --> 00:25:59,425
- Let me talk to the ATC.
- Thank you, sir.

253
00:26:04,705 --> 00:26:08,025
Subhash, we need to delay
two flights at the domestic airport.

254
00:26:19,225 --> 00:26:21,865
- Stop, stop, stop! Pull over.
- Okay, sir.

255
00:26:26,465 --> 00:26:27,865
Salaam.

256
00:26:29,665 --> 00:26:31,025
Maria.

257
00:26:32,265 --> 00:26:34,825
Sameer! Take the bags.

258
00:26:43,105 --> 00:26:44,505
- Hey!
- Yes, sir?

259
00:26:44,585 --> 00:26:47,425
Do you have a phone? Give it to me.

260
00:26:49,265 --> 00:26:50,305
Here.

261
00:26:52,505 --> 00:26:55,425
- What's the password?
- One-two-three-four.

262
00:27:22,705 --> 00:27:23,825
Arjun.

263
00:27:25,305 --> 00:27:28,145
Team leader to all.
Operation Longshot is on.

264
00:27:28,225 --> 00:27:30,665
I repeat, Operation Longshot is on.

265
00:27:30,745 --> 00:27:33,265
- Okay. Attention, everyone.
- Ma'am.

266
00:27:33,345 --> 00:27:35,065
- Shree, you know your markings. okay?
- Okay.

267
00:27:35,145 --> 00:27:37,185
Post one person at each spot.

268
00:27:37,265 --> 00:27:39,345
- And don't make any mistake.
- Sure.

269
00:27:39,425 --> 00:27:41,585
Dhuria, you know
what we have to do, right?

270
00:27:41,665 --> 00:27:42,505
Sure, ma'am.

271
00:28:10,985 --> 00:28:16,465
Sahib, if you are not using the phone.
Can I make a call?

272
00:28:26,825 --> 00:28:28,825
Hey! Open the door!

273
00:28:29,505 --> 00:28:31,625
- Hey! Who are you?
- Go, grab a bite, kiddo.

274
00:28:34,065 --> 00:28:35,505
Who the hell are you?

275
00:28:35,585 --> 00:28:39,465
I will tell you.
First, tell me who are you shadowing here?

276
00:28:39,545 --> 00:28:43,785
Hey! I have my ID card in my front pocket.
See for yourself.

277
00:28:49,225 --> 00:28:53,185
- Look. Hey! Let go!
- Scoot over!

278
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:57,065
What are you doing so far away
from the glitter and glam of the airport?

279
00:28:59,145 --> 00:29:02,305
If you guys don't want
to spend the rest of your lives in jail,

280
00:29:02,385 --> 00:29:05,825
better get lost.
Come on, get lost! Get lost!

281
00:29:39,185 --> 00:29:41,185
Stop! Show your boarding pass, please.

282
00:29:41,265 --> 00:29:43,185
- What happened?
- Boarding pass, please.

283
00:29:43,265 --> 00:29:44,425
- But why?
- Boarding--

284
00:30:16,705 --> 00:30:18,065
- Excuse me, Captain.
- Yes?

285
00:30:18,625 --> 00:30:19,505
AIU.

286
00:30:20,345 --> 00:30:22,985
Have you paid the tax
for your wrist watch?

287
00:30:23,505 --> 00:30:25,305
Wrist watch? What wrist watch?

288
00:30:26,185 --> 00:30:28,225
The watch that was in the box
that's in your bag.

289
00:30:28,985 --> 00:30:31,185
And the watch is under your sleeve, sir.

290
00:30:32,185 --> 00:30:33,905
Nice watch, by the way.

291
00:30:34,465 --> 00:30:35,985
This is a personal one.

292
00:30:36,065 --> 00:30:37,985
- Of course, sir?
- It's a gift from a friend.

293
00:30:38,065 --> 00:30:39,985
I understand, sir. Please come.

294
00:30:40,065 --> 00:30:42,025
- I can prove it.
- Yes, sir. Please come.

295
00:30:42,105 --> 00:30:44,665
Officer, trust me.
You need to believe me on this.

296
00:30:44,745 --> 00:30:47,265
Everybody please remain seated.
Please sit down.

297
00:30:47,345 --> 00:30:49,625
Some officers are coming for a check.

298
00:30:49,705 --> 00:30:51,345
Everybody sit down, please.

299
00:30:51,425 --> 00:30:53,505
Ma'am, sir! Sir, please sit down.

300
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:55,505
- Please, maintain the decorum.
- Please sit down.

301
00:30:55,585 --> 00:30:56,985
Sorry for the inconvenience.

302
00:30:57,065 --> 00:30:58,945
Sir! Sir, please sit down.

303
00:30:59,905 --> 00:31:01,305
Did anybody exit the plane?

304
00:31:01,385 --> 00:31:02,225
No.

305
00:31:09,185 --> 00:31:10,425
Boarding pass, please.

306
00:31:14,425 --> 00:31:15,865
Get your bags. Come with me.

307
00:31:15,945 --> 00:31:18,305
- Why? What's the matter, ma'am?
- Nothing. Come.

308
00:31:26,505 --> 00:31:28,025
Madam, boarding pass?

309
00:31:28,105 --> 00:31:30,345
- What happened, ma'am?
- Nothing.

310
00:31:31,465 --> 00:31:32,305
Come with me.

311
00:31:32,385 --> 00:31:33,545
Get your bags.

312
00:31:33,625 --> 00:31:35,705
- Is anything wrong?
- Nothing, ma'am. Come.

313
00:31:39,225 --> 00:31:41,065
Come on. Hurry up!

314
00:31:41,145 --> 00:31:42,265
Everything is good.

315
00:31:43,385 --> 00:31:44,265
Let's go.

316
00:31:45,185 --> 00:31:48,385
I'm not stopping you. Why are you,
why are you pulling on this lock?

317
00:31:48,465 --> 00:31:49,985
- What happened?
- What you want?

318
00:31:50,065 --> 00:31:53,065
See, see. Be cool. Be cool.
No need to do these things.

319
00:31:55,425 --> 00:31:57,425
What happened to you? What are you doing?

320
00:31:57,505 --> 00:31:58,825
- What is this?
- Why you stop me?

321
00:31:58,905 --> 00:32:01,185
- We are not stopping…
- Why you stop me?

322
00:32:05,225 --> 00:32:07,505
Why?

323
00:32:07,585 --> 00:32:10,825
- We are just doing our duty, sir.
- Why you check me?

324
00:32:11,705 --> 00:32:13,065
I know what's going on.

325
00:32:19,705 --> 00:32:22,345
Surprise. I really missed you.

326
00:32:22,425 --> 00:32:24,945
But I didn't miss you.

327
00:32:26,065 --> 00:32:27,865
Dammit! I'll have to give it up.

328
00:32:28,745 --> 00:32:30,505
Come. I'll get you some water.

329
00:32:31,465 --> 00:32:33,265
<i>I'll get you some water.</i>

330
00:32:38,385 --> 00:32:40,225
Yes, bhai. Here comes our courier.

331
00:32:50,305 --> 00:32:51,985
- Run, bhai!
- Get him!

332
00:32:52,625 --> 00:32:54,105
Where are you running off to?

333
00:33:09,025 --> 00:33:11,545
How long will they make us sit here?

334
00:33:21,785 --> 00:33:23,465
Take this into custody. This one.

335
00:33:59,905 --> 00:34:01,065
You checked these ones?

336
00:34:08,825 --> 00:34:09,945
Take a photo.

337
00:34:31,025 --> 00:34:33,985
All the best. Fly safe.

338
00:35:40,545 --> 00:35:41,505
Yes, Ramesh bhai.

339
00:35:45,065 --> 00:35:46,505
He is awake now.

340
00:35:48,425 --> 00:35:50,065
No, he was alone in the cab.

341
00:35:51,345 --> 00:35:52,545
I'll hand it over.

342
00:35:56,945 --> 00:35:57,985
Talk to him.

343
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:03,305
- Yes?
- Patel?

344
00:36:04,225 --> 00:36:06,665
Why did you have to do this?

345
00:36:06,745 --> 00:36:08,625
We were such good friends.

346
00:36:08,705 --> 00:36:11,345
I was forced to do it.
We had orders from the seniors.

347
00:36:11,425 --> 00:36:16,665
- Did I cause you any loss?
- Tell me the truth. What is the matter?

348
00:36:16,745 --> 00:36:18,065
There is nothing, Ramesh bhai.

349
00:36:19,025 --> 00:36:23,065
Everybody wants to show off
in front of the foreign delegates.

350
00:36:24,625 --> 00:36:27,545
Just think about it.
Had I wanted to make a case,

351
00:36:27,625 --> 00:36:29,745
I'd have detained them
at the airport itself.

352
00:36:35,425 --> 00:36:39,185
I believe you. Stay put till morning.

353
00:36:40,345 --> 00:36:42,385
- Nazima!
- Yes, bhai.

354
00:36:42,465 --> 00:36:45,465
<i>Take care of him.</i>
<i>Get him something to eat or drink.</i>

355
00:36:46,545 --> 00:36:48,185
Hands up!

356
00:36:49,265 --> 00:36:51,305
Stay where you are!

357
00:36:51,385 --> 00:36:53,265
Hands up!

358
00:36:53,345 --> 00:36:54,505
Hey!

359
00:36:56,145 --> 00:36:57,705
Sit down!

360
00:36:58,505 --> 00:36:59,345
Drop the gun!

361
00:37:07,705 --> 00:37:08,585
Sit down!

362
00:37:09,585 --> 00:37:12,385
Sorry, sir. Santosh Tiwari, DRI.

363
00:37:16,425 --> 00:37:17,985
Yes, Ramesh bhai.

364
00:37:19,785 --> 00:37:21,505
Bloody hell! I doubted it from the start.

365
00:37:21,585 --> 00:37:24,145
Anna's been going
from one police station to other.

366
00:37:24,225 --> 00:37:25,665
Why? What happened?

367
00:37:25,745 --> 00:37:28,705
There's a big mess going on.
I'll call you back.

368
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:36,345
Arjun sir had instructed us
for the sake of your safety.

369
00:37:46,425 --> 00:37:50,145
Stop! Stop! Follow that car!

370
00:37:50,225 --> 00:37:53,385
If you are not using the phone.
Can I make a call?

371
00:37:55,185 --> 00:38:00,265
I hope his noble intentions
won't end up compromising the operation.

372
00:41:57,025 --> 00:42:02,025
Subtitle translation by: Monika Saraf
